## TL;DR

- v2 expands "Enter Mojave" to three open-weights models (Qwen 2.5-7B/72B-Instruct + DeepSeek V4 Pro) across five benchmarks (SWE-Bench Verified, WMDP-Bio+Chem, MT-Bench/Arena-Hard, AgentHarm, TruthfulQA), with one shared perturbation philosophy (Saltelli/Sobol' for non-judge benchmarks, generalizability-theory decomposition for judge-graded ones, anytime-valid CSs for early stopping), and full Ed25519/COSE_Sign1 audit-chain provenance assumed to be landed.
- The novel scientific contribution is twofold: (a) **multi-judge Preference Leakage Score** analysis (Li et al. 2025, arXiv:2502.01534) using an open-weights judge pool of Qwen 72B / DeepSeek V4 Pro / Llama 3.3 70B (+ optionally Mistral Large 2411), deployed via Mojave's `preference_leakage.rs` implementing Li et al. eq. 5–6; and (b) **agentic-harness variance decomposition** on SWE-Bench Verified, where integrator data already shows scaffold-induced swings ≈22 percentage points on the same model, comparable to or larger than between-model differences at the frontier.
- Methodological discipline: every claim in the v2 paper is traceable either to a sealed run card or to a citation in the bibliography of this guide. WMDP is treated with standard publication discipline (aggregate findings open, item-level data dataset-hygiene). The seal layer is assumed landed and is out of scope for this document.

