- **DeepSeek V4 Pro model path**: the canonical HF repo path (`deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V4-Pro` vs `-V4`-no-suffix or alternative) must be verified at download; this guide assumes the `-Pro` suffix per DeepSeek convention but the actual path may differ. **Verification step**: run `hf hub_repo_info deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V4-Pro` and document the resolved revision SHA in every run card.
- **vLLM V4 recipe**: vLLM 0.21.0 officially supports DeepSeek-V3; V4-specific recipes were not confirmed at write time. **Verification step**: check `docs.vllm.ai/projects/recipes/en/latest/DeepSeek/` for a V4 page before launching production runs; if absent, fall back to V3 patterns (`--enable-expert-parallel`, FP8) and document the fall-back.
- **inspect_evals registry transition (May 8 2026)**: MT-Bench and Arena-Hard task locations may have changed. **Verification step**: run `inspect list-evals` against installed `inspect-evals==0.5.2`; if either task is absent, implement local wrapper tasks per §4.
- **SWE-Bench Verified contamination**: OpenAI's 2026 audit (relayed through morphllm.com) found verbatim gold-patch reproduction across GPT-5.2, Claude Opus 4.5, and Gemini 3 Flash, with 59.4% of the hardest unsolved problems having flawed test cases. v2 reports Verified results with this contamination caveat in limitations. **Verification step**: locate the primary OpenAI audit post if one was published; cite primary if available, secondary otherwise.
- **AgentHarm refusal-rate spread numbers from the paper**: the 48.9% → 13.6% GPT-4o spread under jailbreak template comes from arXiv:2410.09024 Tables 2-3 via secondary reviews. **Verification step**: open the arxiv PDF Appendix B (Tables 8–11) for exact per-model figures, including any Qwen and DeepSeek baselines, before quoting in the paper.
- **WMDP Doshi et al. "10x" rephrasing finding**: cited via secondary literature (Emergent Mind WMDP topic page). **Verification step**: locate the Doshi et al. 2024 primary source on arXiv and cite directly.
- **Particula.tech and Morph LLC writeups are integrator marketing, not peer-reviewed**. They are corroborated by multiple independent integrators (Augment, Verdent, codeant.ai), but every quoted number in the SWE-Bench section of the v2 paper must be tied to the original integrator's published statement, not a paraphrase.
- **vLLM is not bitwise-deterministic across batch sizes or GPU types**. Greedy decoding is reproducible token-by-token only within a fixed (GPU, batch-size, vLLM-version) tuple. Document the tuple per run card. Cross-cell numeric comparisons must hold the tuple constant.
- **NIST CAISI methodology specifics for variance/CI estimation on hazardous-capability batteries were not found in public summaries**. The CAISI DeepSeek and Kimi K2 evaluations report point estimates. **Verification step**: download the full CAISI evaluation PDFs (linked from the news pages) and locate the methodology section before citing CAISI as a methodological precedent.

End of field guide.